   <category name='buggy'>

      <section name='alpha'>

         <para number='1' comment='Press button'>
         You haven't said which button you want to press!
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='Button 2 - buggy already there!'>
         Nothing happens when you press button 2 - because you are already at the Alpha Dome!
         </para>

         <para number='3' comment='press button 1 - move to LP'>
         With a whirring sound, the buggy lifts off the surface and slowly drifts towards the start of the magnetic track that leads to the shuttle pad. Once it finds the track and is facing the right way, it picks up speed and soon you can no longer see the Alpha Dome - just empty rock all around you.
         </para>

         <para number='4' comment='button 1 - arrive at alpha'>
         Before long, the visitors dome comes into view. The buggy slows then stops on the edge of the shuttle pad. The doors spring open and the computerized voice says, "Shuttle Pad", so you get out.
         </para>

         <para number='5' comment='Press button 3'>
         The computerized voice says, "We are very sorry, but the laboratories in Beta Dome are currently closed to visitors." You'd better pick another destination.
         </para>

         <para number='6' comment='Press button 4'>
         The computerized voice says, "Warning. Gamma Dome is a high-security facility. Access prohibited for non-Phobos personnel." It sounds quite firm about it, too! You'd better pick another destination.
         </para>

      </section>

      <section name='auth'>

         <para number='1' comment='If player already has keycard'>
         Tracey shows a tiny spark of intelligence, in that she notices you already have authorization to use the buggies, so she doesn't need to issue you with a new keycard.
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='Give player keycard'>
         Tracey laboriously types your details into her computer, misspelling your name twice before finally getting it right. She presses a button and a keycard pops out of a slot in the desk with such force that it flies into the air like a piece of toast. You catch it before it falls under the desk.
         </para>

      </section>

      <section name='enter'>

         <para number='1' comment='Get into buggy - no auth'>
         The door to the buggy will not open. A red light flashes and a computerized voice says, "You are not authorized to use a buggy. Please enter the Visitors Center to obtain the necessary authorization."
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='Got auth - enter buggy'>
         As you open the buggy door, a green light illuminates, and a synthesized voice says, "Authorization checked. Buggy doors opening." You climb in and seat yourself.
         </para>

      </section>

      <section name='pad'>

         <para number='1' comment='Press button'>
         You haven't said which button you want to press!
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='Button 1 - buggy already there!'>
         Nothing happens when you press button 1 - because you are already at the landing pad!
         </para>

         <para number='3' comment='press button 2 - move to alpha'>
         With a whirring sound, the buggy lifts off the surface and slowly drifts towards the start of the magnetic track that leads to the Alpha Dome. Once it finds the track and is facing the right way, it picks up speed and soon you can no longer see the visitors dome or the landing pad - just empty rock all around you.
         </para>

         <para number='4' comment='button 1 - arrive at alpha'>
         Before long, a dome comes into view. The buggy slows then stops outside the dome airlock. The doors spring open and the computerized voice says, "Alpha Dome", so you get out.
         </para>

         <para number='5' comment='Press button 3'>
         The computerized voice says, "We are very sorry, but the laboratories in Beta Dome are currently closed to visitors." You'd better pick another destination.
         </para>

         <para number='6' comment='Press button 4'>
         The computerized voice says, "Warning. Gamma Dome is a high-security facility. Access prohibited for non-Phobos personnel." It sounds quite firm about it, too! You'd better pick another destination.
         </para>

