   <category name='food'>

      <section name='morph'>

         <para number='1' comment='Buy food - Morph Bar - 340'>
         A waitdroid deposits a plate of morphood in front of you - a foodstuff invented on Phobos, needless to say. As you watch, it changes from solid to liquid and back again, the color changes, and - as you find out when you pluck up the courage to actually eat some - so does the taste.
         </para>

         <para number='2'>
         You place some in your mouth and feel it change disconcertingly from steak, to chocolate, to soup, to ice cream, to bread... each mouthful does the same, leaving you reeling from the very strange gustatory experience.
         </para>

         <para number='3' comment='Not enuff groats'>
         You are so hard up you cannot even afford to buy yourself a meal - and Phobos is not run as a charity!
         </para>

      </section>

      <section name='noshery'>

         <para number='1' comment='Buy food - Noshery - 586'>
         Seating yourself at one of the communal tables, you ask for whatever is on offer today as the main meal. With a buzzing noise and a flash of light, a plate materializes in front of you containing a large slice of steak and kidney pudding: thick, meaty chunks of steak, tender slices of lamb kidneys, all in a rich gravy, surrounded by a fluffy case of suet pastry. It is served with a heap of mashed potato and some minted peas.
         </para>

         <para number='2'>
         You eat it all and contemplate licking the remains of the delicious gravy off the plate, before reluctantly deciding it wouldn't be polite.
         </para>

         <para number='3' comment='Not enuff groats'>
         Only Phobos staff can eat in the Noshery without paying - if you don't have any money, you will just have to go hungry.
         </para>

      </section>

