   <category name='objects'>

      <section name='keycard'>

         <para number='1' comment='Examine keycard'>
         The keycard authorizes you to use a buggy to travel between the domes on Phobos. The card has biometric properties and has acclimated itself to your uniqueness: it is made out in the name of %s.
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='Drop keycard'>
         As part of the Galactic Administration's campaign against litter, the keycard is super-bio-degradable - it is designed to disintegrate completely on contact with the ground. You can now confirm that this anti-litter initiative works perfectly.
         </para>

      </section>

      <section name='tracey'>

         <para number='1' comment='Kiss/hug/grope/get Tracey'>
         She may be stupid, but she is adept at avoiding unwanted amorous attentions. As you lean over the desk towards her, she backs away and picks up her comm unit. "Uh-huh," she says, wagging a finger at you. "No touching, or I will call security."
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='hello'>
         Tracey repeats her mantra: "Welcome-to-Phobos-my-name-is-Tracey-how-may-I-help-you." She looks at you briefly with a vacant stare, waiting for you to tell her what you want.
         </para>

         <para number='3' comment='tracey/who'>
         "Tracey Alamanadina," she introduces herself, "And I am pleased to meet you, %s. I am the receptionist for The Phobos Pharmaceuticals Cooperative Visitors Center...." She stumbles a little over the long words... "and I am here to help you."
         </para>

         <para number='4'>
         That seems to be the end of her official welcome; she relaxes slightly now she is not having to recite what she has obviously memorized with great difficulty, and starts talking more naturally, using what passes for teen slang these days. "I've been working here for decs and it's never a dull moment, you know?" She gives a little giggle and snaps her chewing gum. "The scientist guys, they come up with new stuff all the time, you know?"
         </para>

         <para number='5' comment='reception/job'>
         "All my buds thought it was real pash, me getting such an exotic post, you know?" Tracey tells you with a high-pitched giggle. "They're stuck in these, like, drear places with totally boring accountants and such. Real terror, you know?" You nod to indicate that you do, indeed, know.
         </para>

         <para number='6'>
         "My Unc got me this post, he's something crucial in the government, you know? He said it would be good for me to, what was it, broaden my hor... hori... something, anyway. I didn't want to say gbye to my buds, but now I've made some new buds here, and they really are pash, quite the biz, you know?"
         </para>

         <para number='7' comment='scientists'>
         "They are some wild guys, always doing weird stuff, but they come up with these things that make loads of groats for the co-op, you know? The astro-turf, living computers, living fur, clothes made out of real flowers..." She shrugs, drawing your attention to her amazing dress.
         </para>

         <para number='8'>
         "People think scientists are nerdy and all that, but some of them here are real ruggedy, you know? And they have great parties." She smiles and giggles.
         </para>

         <para number='9' comment='Phobos/where'>
         "It is odd living on such a small planet. If they didn't have the fake gravity thingy it would be real square. I was brought up on Earth and I miss not going outside, you know? But the scientists have come up with all kinds of growing stuff that stops the rock being too sad."
         </para>

         <para number='10' comment='Earth'>
         "Earth is my real home," she confides. "I'll go back there one day and get married and settle down. This is just temp. I mean, Earth's the only real planet in the system, you know? The rest are just colonies. Earth's where the important stuff happens."
         </para>

         <para number='11' comment='buggy'>
         "If you want to use a buggy you need a keycard. I can't just give you one, you need to formally ask me for authorization. Sorry. It's the rules. Sorry. I can't break the rules. It's more than my job's worth. Sorry."
         </para>

         <para number='12' comment='dress/clothes'>
         "Oh yeah, it's really wack, you know? Just one of the amazing things cooked up by those scientists. The dress is really made of real flowers, and the blossoms move around as they follow the light. It lasts about a week then the petals start dropping off, which is a bit of a mizz, but I guess they'll get that bug ironed out soon, you know?"
         </para>

         <para number='13' comment='ming'>
         "Who?" Tracey has obviously never heard of the ex-Emperor; the look on her face is one of complete and utter incomprehension.
         </para>

         <para number='14' comment='emperor'>
         She giggles, "Now you're being silly. We don't have an Emperor any more, we have the Galactic Administration. Unc Silus does something in their headquarters. He works on a real high floor, the view is really wack, you know?"
         </para>

         <para number='15' comment='galactic admin/GA'>
         "When I want to go back to Earth my Unc Silus will get me a job in the GA HQ, he says. That'll be pash, you know?"
         </para>

         <para number='16' comment='flowers'>
         She smiles at you broadly. "You noticed my dress! Yes, it really is made of real live flowers. Amazing, you know?"
         </para>

         <para number='17' comment='computers'>
         "The living computers are creepy, you know?" Tracey tells you. "They have feelings and moods and stuff, just like real people do. I don't know if I like that. I mean, what if they just don't feel like doing stuff one day, you know? I mean, what if a computer got in a bad mood, you know? I mean, when I'm in a bad mood I sometimes throw things, but a computer might mess up something serious, you know?" She shudders at the thought.
         </para>

         <para number='18' comment='furs'>
         "Living furs are totally wack," Tracey says. "I love them, they're like a cross between a blanket and a pet. I've got three in my room, and I just wrap myself up in them and it's like being in the middle of a heap of furry animals, all warm and soft and snug..."
         </para>

         <para number='19' comment='living'>
         "They specialize in living stuff here," Tracey explains. "Living furs, living computers, and just look at my dress!"
         </para>

         <para number='20' comment='nomatch for Tracey'>
         Tracey stares at you with a look of complete and utter incomprehension on her face. She doesn't understand what you just asked her about.
         </para>

         <para number='21' comment='buds'>
         "They're a real wack crew," Tracey tells you. "There's Jem and Kojo and Fazackerly and Minto and Mandy and Jackie and the four Marys - they're clones you know - and my best bud of all, Bunty." She beams at you, as if she expects you to have heard of these people.
         </para>

         <para number='22' comment='gravity'>
         "Oh, all that science stuff is beyond me," Tracey says with a giggle. "I don't know how the gravity thingy works. You'll have to ask one of the scientists I guess."
         </para>

         <para number='23' comment='unc/silus'>
         "I don't know what it is he does for the Galactic Administration, but it must be real important because he works all the time - I mean, he never takes any time off, you know? And he's always being called in to deal with stuff in the middle of the night, you know? But I don't know what stuff."
         </para>

         <para number='24' comment='help'>
         "That's my job, to help you," Tracey assures you, although the complete lack of any vestige of intelligence in her gaze doesn't fill you with confidence that she will be able to!
         </para>

         <para number='25' comment='clue/magellan/victor'>
         "If you are doing the Magellan Society treasure hunt, I am not supposed to give you any clues. Victor's told me not to try to help you, and what Victor says, I have to do, you know?" She giggles.
         </para>

         <para number='26' comment='dna/sculture/spiral'>
         "Oh, you saw that, did you?" asks Tracey. "Well I guess it's hard to miss, hanging there right inside the entrance, you know? One of my buds explained to me what it was supposed to be, but I didn't really understand. Something to do with biology, I think..." she looks at you blankly.
         </para>

         <para number='27' comment='dome'>
         "There's four domes on Phobos," Tracey explains. "This dome is the Visitors Center, then there's Alpha, Beta and Gamma domes. There's buggies that let you drive to the other domes, they are too far to walk."
         </para>

         <para number='28' comment='alpha'>
         "Alpha Dome is where we all live, all the permanent people on Phobos, that's the scientists and the other ones like me."
         </para>

         <para number='29' comment='beta'>
         "Beta Dome is the main laboratory dome. Normally you could visit there, but it's off-limits just now because of some security problem or something."
         </para>

         <para number='30' comment='gamma'>
         "Oh, you can never go to Gamma Dome," Tracey exclaims. "Even I can't go there, it's totally out of bounds, you know? That's where they do the dangerous stuff and the top secret stuff, you know?"
         </para>

         <para number='31' comment='morph'>
         "Oh, it's over there," Tracey says, waving in a vaguely westerly direction. "I don't drink there, it's for visitors, you know? Well, not usually, although when my Unc Silus comes to call we grab a bite there to save time, because he's always so busy, you know? But I never get drunk in the Morph Bar, the decor is just too strange to mix with alcohol, you know?"
         </para>

         <para number='32' comment='dorm/accommodation'>
         "The dorms are that way," Tracey tells you and points south. "There's nobody staying there at the moment so if you want to crash for a while just go on in."
         </para>

         <para number='33' comment='date'>
         "Are you asking me for a date?" Tracey giggles. "Oh, that's so sweet of you, but I don't go out with strangers."
         </para>

         <para number='34' comment='bye'>
         "Have a nice day," Tracey says with a big, bright smile, then she spits out her chewing gum and pops a fresh stick into her mouth, and turns her attention back to her magazine.
         </para>

         <para number='35' comment='Ex Tracey'>
         Tracey is very pretty, and dressed in an outrageously fashionable outfit that seems to have been made out of flowers. It even gives off a floral perfume, too. There is not the slightest sign of intelligence in her eyes.
         </para>

      </section>

